{{Otheruses|Tanner}}
{{Quote|The guns, dating from the Old Republic's early Manderon Period, are over 6,000 years old. They are said to have been created on Brentaal by Andel Tanner, a prominent inventor of the era.|A news report by TriNebulon News|<ref name="Journal4">{{JournalCite|4|Galaxywide NewsNets}}</ref>}}
'''Andel Tanner''' was a prominent [[Artisan/Legends|inventor]] who lived during the early [[Manderon Period]],<ref name="Journal4" /> an era that lasted from [[7000 BBY]] to [[5000 BBY/Legends|5000 BBY]].<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> It was said that a pair of [[Slugthrower pistol/Legends|slugthrower pistols]], which were more than 6,000 [[Standard year/Legends|years]] old by the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], had been created by Tanner on<ref name="Journal4" /> the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core Worlds]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="TEA" /> [[Brentaal IV/Legends|Brentaal IV]]. That claim was mentioned in a [[0 ABY/Legends|35:7:29]] [[Media/Legends|news]] report by [[TriNebulon News/Legends|TriNebulon News]] covering the [[Thief/Legends|theft]] of the [[Pistol/Legends|pistols]] from the famed [[Musician/Legends|musician]] [[Fitz Roi]].<ref name="Journal4" />

==Behind the scenes==
Andel Tanner was mentioned in the "[[Galaxywide NewsNets]]" feature of the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 4|fourth issue]] of [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'' magazine, which was published in [[November]] [[1994]]. The feature was authored by [[Paul Sudlow]].<ref name="Journal4" />

